HEADWORD: Slabby
<hw>Slab"by</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <amorph>[<pos>Compar.</pos>
<adjf>Slabbier</adjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>superl.</pos>
<adjf>Slabbiest</adjf>.]</amorph> <ety>[See <er>Slab</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Thick; viscous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They present you with a cup, and you must drink of a
<qex>slabby</qex> stuff.</q> <rj><qau>Selden.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Sloppy; slimy; miry. See <er>Sloppy</er>.</def>
<rj><au>Gay.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slab-sided</ent>⟦br⟧
